# UI/UX Pro Max

## Review Checklist

### Visual Hierarchy
- [ ] Primary action is the most visually prominent element
- [ ] Text sizes follow a clear scale (not arbitrary pixel values)
- [ ] Whitespace is intentional — breathing room, not filler
- [ ] Color draws attention only to what matters

### Interaction Design
- [ ] Every interactive element has a visible hover, focus, and active state
- [ ] Loading states exist for all async operations
- [ ] Empty states are designed (not blank screens)
- [ ] Error states give the user a path forward

### Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA minimum)
- [ ] Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for body text, ≥ 3:1 for large text
- [ ] All interactive elements are keyboard-navigable
- [ ] Focus ring is always visible (never `outline: none` without a replacement)
- [ ] Images have meaningful alt text; decorative images have `alt=""`
- [ ] Form inputs have associated `<label>` elements

### Responsive Design
- [ ] Mobile-first: design for 375px, then scale up
- [ ] Touch targets are ≥ 44×44px on mobile
- [ ] No horizontal scroll at any breakpoint
- [ ] Typography is readable without zoom at 320px

### Performance UX
- [ ] Above-the-fold content loads first (LCP < 2.5s)
- [ ] No layout shift on load (CLS < 0.1)
- [ ] Skeleton screens preferred over spinners for content areas

## Output Format
When reviewing, output:
1. **Critical issues** (blocks usability) — fix immediately
2. **Major issues** (degrades experience) — fix in this sprint
3. **Minor improvements** (polish) — address when possible
4. **What's working well** — so it doesn't accidentally get changed
